name: ESG Scores Data
description:
This dataset has ESG scores for different ESG factors for companies. There are 5 kind of files for each factor for each stock:

â€¢ Pulse files: The files provide scores that measures short-term, real-time performance and focus on events of the day
â€¢ Insight files:  The files provide scores that are derived from pulse score using an exponentially weighted moving average (WMA) and focuses on measuring long-term performance
â€¢ Momentum files: Focus on measuring the trend of a company. These scores are derived from Insight Scores by measuring the slope of insight scores.
â€¢ Volume files: Measures by company the number of unique articles, as well as the number of categories scored daily
â€¢ Volume ttm  files: Measures by company the number of unique articles, as well as the number of categories scored over last 12 months

It contains fundamental data at a more granular level and thus can be a source of alpha ideas. Data fields with "dei" refer to company related metadata, those with "monetary" refer to numerical financial information, and those with "non-monetary" refer to non-numerical financial information. name: Global Insider Trading Data

The entries of the dataset contains details of each transaction including traded amount, price, currency, transaction type, and so on. The dataset also provides importance of trades and levels of insiders estimated by vendor model. The dataset has relatively short history, backfill is required, and it requires some insights to select speculative trades from those that are not. However, the information in this dataset is unique and one of the most comprehensive in insider category.

name: Edgar forms data
description: Accruals-based method is widely used to analyze earnings quality, detect earnings management, and predict equity return. Accruals are revenues earned or expenses incurred which impact a company's net income on the income statement, although cash related to the transaction has not yet changed hands. For example, if a company overstates its earnings without receiving sufficient cash accordingly for a long time, accruals are consecutively positive, which is a bad sign of earnings quality. Companies with good current earnings quality are more likely to have higher future earnings and stock returns.

description: This dataset calculates market implied values for data provided in erlanger.

name: Risk Parity Method Model
description: The model takes advantage of value factors, risk mitigation techniques, dynamic regime switching algorithm, point-in-time risk parity method, and unique portfolio construction techniques. The model captures the upside of value investing and avoids the underperformance, with a much lower downside risk than conventional value factors.

name: Alternative technical factror models
description: This dataset provides a comprehensive suite of alternative factors that can be used in conjunction with our fundamental and technical factor libraries. This dataset  included hundreds of stock-selection factors based on intellectual properties, corporate regulatory filings, institutional ownership, and more importantly five sector specific data packages (Banks, TMT, REITs and property companies, Health Care, and Energy).

name: ETF Based Equity Factors
description: Information based on the ETFs which include each stocks as underlying assets.

name: Stock Selection from Accounting-based Factors
description: The dataset derived from stock-selection factor model based on representative accounting variables like profitability and financial leverage/liquidity ratios

name: Inflation based stock selection model
description: The model is expected to generate signal in an inflationary environment and remains resilient should inflation retreat. By construction, the model focuses on stock-specific idiosyncratic opportunities, by neutralizing major risk factors (country, sector, size, and beta) and style factors (e.g., cyclical value, price momentum, and volatility).

name: Sensitivity to the Inflation Change
description: (Sensitivity to the Inflation Change) strategy that incorporates many insights discovered in this research. The model offers a stock-level sensitivity estimate to expected inflation proxied by change of breakeven rate and leverages the elastic net machine learning regression.

name: Interest Rate Sensitivity Measures
description: FLEIR stands for Forward-Looking Exposure to Interest Rates Model. This model contains a stock-level interest rate sensitivity measure called the FLEIR, based on the well-known discounted cash flow model (DCF). The method is to simulate various discount rates and assess how sensitive company DCF valuations are to increasing rates. The DCF model is developed using forward-looking analyst estimate data

name: AI Driven Predictive Model
description: Machine Learning based scores are provided in this dataset, such as: quality, value, momentum, growth and a mixed score field. Each of these scores have an integer value between 1 and 9. The level and behavior of these scores can be used to predict price movements.
researchPapers: [{'title': 'Research Paper 44: A Fibonacci Heap Based Ensemble Model for Stock Price Prediction', 'url': 'https://support.worldquantbrain.com/hc/en-us/community/posts/15770040002199-Research-Paper-44-A-Fibonacci-Heap-Based-Ensemble-Model-for-Stock-Price-Prediction'}]

name: Fundamental Scores
description: This dataset ranks stocks based on fundamental and behavioral factors in 5 categories: Valuation, Growth, Profitability, Momentum and Quality. Within these categories, there are additional metrics that have been identified as being key drivers of stock performance. For example looking at valuation, we consider metrics such as price to earnings, price to book value and many more. The fundamental scores are distributed between 0 and 1, and the data frequency is monthly.
researchPapers: [{'title': 'Research Raper 01: The Momentum of News', 'url': 'https://support.worldquantbrain.com/hc/en-us/community/posts/13954113156503-Research-Raper-01-The-Momentum-of-News'}]

name: Return prediction from conference call
description: Data produced by using advanced AI/deep learning methodologies.

name: ML/AI-Estimates for Analysts' Factor Model
description: This dataset predicts fundamental values using advanced AI/deep learning methodologies.

name: Technical and Fundamental ranking model
description: The dataset are on overall company analysis. The analysis includes fundamental research, portfolio evaluation, and screening tools on over 40,000 global equities. The end-user could enjoy in-depth analysis on a) performance relative to its peers,b) accounting and earnings quality, c) dividend strength and d) likely corporate actions such as dividend changes, share buybacks, and acquisitons. History is monthly up until 2014 and then the periodicity is daily.

name: Non-Financial Metric Models
description: Ratings that quantify non-financial statement factors into metrics that have been demonstrated to drive cash flow, risk. Ratings cover 4500 securities globally. They are based on 6 pillars making up their rating which consists of management, health, welath, earth, equality, and trust.

name: Geographic network based model
description: Price momentum scores based on different models. For capturing the co-movement between fundamentally linked companied, related companies are grouped together by different approaches (e.g. business segment, analyst group, geography, customer-supplier relationshop, etc.). The momentum scores for each grouping approach are generated and a composite model is provided.

name: North America CDS Factor Model
description: Financial derivative that transfers credit risk and factors of financial stability

name: Brand Popularity Data
description: The dataset is derived from 'scraping' web content and determining the number of times that the brand names owned by a corporation are mentioned on any given day.

name: Fundamental & Technical Rank Model
description: This dataset weighs fundamental and technical metrics of each stock dynamically to produce a ranking system. These ranking scores will help better understand the comparative qualities of each stock.

name: NLP Model on Textual Data
description: The dataset contains statistical information of an information procuring website.

name: Analyst estimate prediction data
description: Machine learning driven predictive dataset for fundamental information

name: Analyst Revisions Model Data
description: The dataset provides a stock ranking system that provides a single 1 to 100 daily ranking for various global stocks. In addition, component, regional and business classification scores are provided.

name: Inflation based Equity data
description: The dataset provide a stock-selection model for inflationary environment from analysing the equity factor and historical inflation changes.

name: Fundamental Focus Rank Model
description: This dataset holds ranking of stocks based on fundamental and technical metrics

name: Scorings Data
description: This is a model dataset which scores stocks on various metrics that predict their outperformance or underperformance. The assessment is available over different future time horizons. Various research ideas are used to predict sentiment & downside risk which are then combined together to provide a final score to the stock.
researchPapers: [{'title': 'Research Paper 23: Overvalued Equity and Financing Decisions', 'url': 'https://support.worldquantbrain.com/hc/en-us/community/posts/14983690885911-Research-Paper-23-Overvalued-Equity-and-Financing-Decisions'}]

name: Earnings Quality
description: This model dataset provides with financial statement information and model derived on that. It provides a percentile ranking between 1 and 100 for all stocks on various factors that measure earnings sustainability. It also outputs factors that assess the change in analyst sentiment over future horizons.

name: Analyst Revisions
description: This dataset provides model scores based on analyst estimates. It generates custom scores based on numerous trusted sources for analyst recommendations and targets for price, company fundamentals, growth & others. It outputs raw and processed values, as well as certain important industry ratios.

name: Credit Risk Model
description: This is a credit risk estimate dataset. It evaluates various ideas to provide the final probability estimate of default & scores around it. It takes into consideration the market view of credit risk, financial health of the firm, news around the stock, corporate filings, etc to analyze firmâ€™s financial condition.

name: Structural Credit Risk Model
description: This is a credit risk estimate dataset. It evaluates the market view of firmâ€™s credit risk using a standardized prediction framework. It is shown to be a good predictor of identifying stocks likely to default & provides a better ranking of stocks than other comparable models.

name: EBITDA Estimate Model
description: A company's earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation, and amortization (EBITDA) is a measure of a company's profitability of the operating business only, thus before any effects of indebtedness, state-mandated payments, and costs required to maintain its asset base. This dataset provides near term as well as longer term estimates of EBITDA values.

name: EPS Estimate Model
description: Earnings per shareÂ (EPS) is a figure describing a public company's profit per outstanding share of stock, calculated on a quarterly or annual basis. It indicates how much money a company makes for each share of its stock and is a widely used metric for estimating corporate value. This dataset provides near term as well as longer term prediction of EPS values.
researchPapers: [{'title': 'Research Paper 27: Earnings Uncertainty and Attention', 'url': 'https://support.worldquantbrain.com/hc/en-us/community/posts/15238236130327-Research-Paper-27-Earnings-Uncertainty-and-Attention'}]

name: Earnings Quality Model
description: This model dataset provides a selection factor for global stocks that helps in identification of companies likely to experience especially high/low earnings sustainability over the subsequent months. It decompositions past earnings into sustainable and non-sustainable components to achieve this. It also has values & differences for various factors over different time horizons.

name: Price Momentum Model
description: This dataset provides multiple aspects of stock's price momentum other than traditional momentum factors. It looks into information from multiple dimensions of price momentum to provide unique & comprehensive measures. It has shown to outperform when traditional factors fail. The model translates all the components into percentile scale (1-100).

name: Revenue Estimate Model
description: Revenue is the money generated from normal business operations, it is the top line (or gross income) figure from which costs are subtracted to determine net income. This dataset aggregates the analyst estimation and revision on company's revenue over different time horizons.

name: SmartRatios Model
description: This is a financial health estimate dataset of stocks. It provides a comprehensive view of a firmâ€™s credit condition by analyzing various ratios predictive of credit risk. It outputs estimate of probability of default & maps it to traditional letter ratings. The probabilities are ranked to output percentile scores between 1 and 100.

name: Text Mining Data
description: This dataset uses language analysis technique to evaluate credit risk through multiple directions like news, transcripts, filings, and research. It is shown to provide a more accurate default risk estimation than standard benchmark. It provides ratings, probability of default & article counts for each evaluation direction in integer format, modeled through percentile scores in 1-100 range (higher number means less likely probability of default). The alpha signal is different from others. For some regions there is occasional coverage drop so check performance stability.

name: Growth Valuation Model
description: This dataset is a stock ranking model that sort companies based on valuation ratios. It looks at different valuation ratios & intelligently combines them into a single comprehensive measure of relative valuation. Each ratio is weighed to ensure most important ratio for a stock has greatest influence in final score. It blends information from both reported actuals & analyst estimates over quarterly, semi-annual or annual horizons.

name: Valuation Momentum Data
description: This dataset provide models for the momentums of prices and intrinsic values. It cpmbines separate datasets to make one exceptionally strong stock ranking model

name: Ranking & Recommendation Data
description: This is a model dataset based on ranking of financial advice published online by analysts around the world. It uses advanced natural language processing algorithms and machine learning to measure performance of investment advised published online. It builds a profile of analyst & blogger recommendations and their credibility. It takes into account the timeliness of these recommendations & the quality of source as well.

name: CDS Based Model Data
description: The dataset provides output of statistical models that evaluate credit default swap (CDS) value that captures the market's sentiment about a company's risk.

name: Insider Model for the US
description: The dataset contains major factors found to be significant in studies on the relationship between insider trading and subsequent stock returns.

name: Insider Model V2 for the US
description: Data fields of this dataset are result of a model providing market participant activity scores. The assigned score is based on criteria found to be significant in studies on the relationship between insider trading and subsequent stock returns

name: Insider Data for the US
description: Data on equity transactions by insiders which include officer, director, person with a policy-making role in a company, or a beneficial owner of a companyâ€™s stock. Insidersâ€™ stock transaction activities and holdings offer insights that can reflect corporate insidersâ€™ views on their companiesâ€™ stocks, which may serve as a buy or sell signal in the stock.

name: Systematic Risk Metrics
description: This is a risk-model data offering several metrics that can be used to quantify & identify risk. It provides technical information like beta, correlation and unsystematic risk all relative to SPY and systematic risk (also known as idiosyncratic risk) - each for different time periods.

name: Creditworthiness Risk Measure Model
description: This dataset provides risk measures for public firms, non-public firms, U.S. banks, and sovereign counterparties which can be used to assess credit worthiness of an entire credit portfolio or on a single name basis. Inputs to the models include company specific attributes, industry related measures and relevant macro-economic factors. It provides a full term structure of risk for both corporate and sovereign credit names based upon a multiple models approach.

name: Technical Indicators
description: This data includes technical indicators and ranks based on price and volume.

name: Stock Reports Plus
description: This dataset provides stock rating based on research reports. The output helps in spotting companies with ratings changes, bullish or bearish price movements, earnings surprises, and solid reported fundamentals.

name: News Direct-feed Data

name: Dow Jones News Analytics Data
description: The Sentiment Analysis Engine (SAE) is a software for producing Sentiment Indices that gauge different emotions of the public to financial assets traded in exchange markets worldwide. Specific emotions about an asset are detected in texts by matching words of text with keywords from an emotional dictionary.

name: News Analytics on Equities
description: This dataset provides real-time news and its numerical interpretation on financial events from multiple news sources. This enables quantitative trading framework to exploit the power of news to capitalize on market inefficiency.

name: Financial News Data
description: The dataset provides NLP model output for articles from a financial news website.

name: News Analytics Data
description: The dataset consists of real-time news analytics from Internet and third-party services. The analysis model quantifies news with sentiment label, event/topic categories, and classification confidence scores.

name: News Analytic Model Data
description: The dataset provides datafields from news analytic model output applying on various sources like text news, blogs, and sentiment.

name: US/AMR news data
description: This vendor provides an original content financial news service and delivers 1,000+ articles per day across 120+ categories. Corporate news categories include announcements, earnings, analyst rating changes, dividends, M&As, insider transactions and more.

name: Real-time Trading Event Data
description: The dataset provides trading alert about stock-related unusual trading behaviour

name: Relevant News Analytics Data
description: The dataset includes rich structured information and potential signals on both scheduled and unscheduled news events. It quantifies positive and negative perceptions on facts and opinions reported in the news. It continuously analyzes relevant information from all major real-time newswires, online media and trustworthy sources to produce real-time news analytics.

name: Global Media News Data
description: The dataset provides news and information from the leading global media organizations.

name: News Feed Analytics Data
description: This dataset provides news headlines with various numerical measurements related to the events including market response to the news. Headlines could be analyzed using NLP techniques and related numeric variables would be useful as filters or sentiments.

name: Web News Analytics Data
description: Analyze articles/news from leading publishers and web aggregators.

name: Aggregared News Data
description: The dataset provides aggregated news from different sources and filters out the duplicated news based on news content.

name: Conference call data
description: Information on company's conference call, such as the type of call, the number of participants on the company side and analyst side, the number of talks/questions/sentences/paragraphs/words/chars in presentation part and Q&A part respsectively. Also it generates keywords occurrence and each position from a specific dictionary. Based on this conference call, a researcher can generate unique signals predicting sentiment on the company after the conference call event.

name: Newa analystic data
description: This dataset provides access to events & news that might affect the market. This dataset divides the list of such events in 3 different categories & together they cover a comprehensive list of all important events. The daily event contains list of events that occur on a day to day basis, key development fields are sensitive events, future events are consolidated in the third category. There is also consolidated information from various sources on earnings release & different types of event in this dataset.

name: Intermediate News Data
description: The dataset provides intermediate news data that aggregate from multiple different sources of news data

name: Corporate Events Data
description: The dataset is a collection of corporate events and event notifications including earnings release dates, sales results, conferences, and shareholder and board meeting information. It can be combine with analyst data to create signal.

name: Webpage View Statistics
description: The dataset is a collection of view statistics for a webpage associated with a company. There are reports show correlation between page views/searches and trading volume which may leads to alpha signal.

name: Real Time News Feed Data
description: Combines various text new feeds from multiple sources to result useful data points to captre stock selection signals
researchPapers: [{'title': 'Research Paper 25: The Momentum of News', 'url': 'https://support.worldquantbrain.com/hc/en-us/community/posts/15154747128471-Research-Paper-25-The-Momentum-of-News'}]

name: Earnings Call Transcript Data
description: The dataset provieds a rich set of scores, tags, and other structured information in real-time after the earnings call transcripts are available

name: Sentiment Analysis from DNN
description: The dataset derived from applying neural network models to various textual datasets.

name: Headline Sentiment Analysis using DNN
description: The dataset derived from applying neural network models to news headlines for sentiment analysis

name: News Sentiment Analysis using DNN
description: The dataset derived from applying neural network models to web news dataset for sentiment analysis

name: Smart Conference call transcript data
description: Conference call transcript data provides mainly long texture content. To help better utilize the long string, we structure it and make stats on many aspects and levels. Finally we output hundreads of numerical fields. There are 3 parts. The first makes some basic stats like words/sentences in the transcripts, and also attendances of people, and so on. the second calculates the readability scores of transcripts. the third calculates the sentiment scores of people in the conference call.

name: Aggregation News Data
description: The dataset aggregates news data from different sources. It removes duplicated news, and merge similar news across sources.

name: Standardized Financial News Categorization
description: No dataset description

name: VWAP Tick Data
description: The dataset is computed end of day VWAP using tick data.

description: This is a statistical grouping data. The prefix "cx" in the field name defines group count such as 2,5,10,20,50. The coverage of fields is also put in their names like sta1_top500c10 has coverage only in TOP500.

name: Global Daily Pricing Data
description: Global daily pricing and reference data for Global Equities, Indices, Warrants, FX, Money Market Securities, Futures, Equity Options, Options on Futures. Corporate Actions such as Dividends, Splits, Mergers & Acquisitions for Global Equities

name: Alternate Industry Classification
description: This is a statistical grouping data. The prefix "cx" in the field name defines the group count such as 2,5,10,20,50. The coverage of fields is also put in their names like sta2_top500_fact1_c10 has coverage only in TOP500.

name: Index Market Data
description: The dataset includes global Index market data

name: Fund Holding Data
description: The dataset provides reported list of holdings by funds. Mutual funds have 60 days after their quarter ends to file their holdings with the SEC.

name: Relation data from Form 10-K and 20-F
description: This data includes manually inputted relations extracted from Form 10-K and Form 20-F

name: Corporate Action Dataset
description: This dataset looks at corporate events that can affect stock prices, such as delisting, merger, stock splits, etc. One can analyze the effect of corporate actions on stock prices and develop alphas based on event-driven opportunities.

name: Securities Lending Insight Data
description: The dataset provides list of metrics, covering lending fee, short interest, it also supplies two unique factors, measuring crowding and short squeeze risks.

name: Beta Risk Factors
description: The dataset contains many important variables that is used in the time series regression to caclulate beta, such as adv20, growth, book value. The beta factor, beta industry and intercept value represents the output of the model.

name: Fundamentals related Risk Factors
description: 6 major financial-accountability categories of risk factors : Financial & Corporate, Legal & Regulatory, Production, Technology & Innovation, Ability to Sell and Macro & Political

name: Forecast Data
description: The dataset provides the standardized computations of weights, volatility, the beta of each stock with respect to market average, market average returns, and market residual returns.

name: Classification based on Business description
description: Classifying stocks on the basis of the their annual business descriptions

name: ETF Risk Data
description: The dataset provides alpha and risk data from ETF. ETF signals are uncorrelated to traditional factors and active strategies, offering considerable diversification benefit.

name: Research Sentiment Data
description: This dataset holds earning estimation/surprise and sentiment of each company in USA.

name: Search Engine Data
description: The dataset captures captures the search trends for keywords associated with each stocks. The data offers the option to compare search trends for companies for the last 10 years worth of history.

name: Social Media Stock Data
description: The dataset provides data from a social media platform for investing ideas.

name: Fund Flow Data
description: The dataset shows insights into the flows into or out of each fund

name: Short Interest Model
description: This is a model dataset that gives short interest data of stocks. It mainly covers USA stocks but also has some limited coverage in other regions. Investment hypothesis states that stocks with higher/lower number of shares shorted will underperform/outperform their peers. This data normalizes short interest levels across country, market cap, and sector categories and also provides institutional ownership percentage, volatility levels and short squeeze level for stocks.

name: Securities Lending Files Data
description: The data consists of loans of securities by lending agents, third party lenders and beneficial owners and borrows by prime brokers and asset managers. The transaction level data from the data providers are aggregated across providers into security level data. Data on the supply of shares available for lending at lending programs are used to calculate utilization rates for individual securities across these lending programs.

name: Qualitative company data
description: The dataset offers in-depth qualitative information about companies around the world to enhance investment selection.

name: SmartHoldings Model
description: This dataset is a global stock selection model that ranks stocks based on the predicted future change in institutional ownership. It looks into various funds and creates their purchasing profile based on the underlying fundamental or technical factors of the companies it buys. Aggregation over different funds help predict future probable changes in institutional ownership of the stocks.

name: Short Selling Model
description: The dataset combines features obtained from short contracts to estimate risk-neutral returns. The factors include loan rates, volume of loans, age of loans, their differences over time, and so on, and derived factors. The method of combination differs among different type of contracts and regions, and all factors are standardized to percentile. The combined score is a strong alpha mode.
